data.name: Keep Info Up-To-Date
data.description:
A company asks its employees to update their personal information once a year. They do this by submitting a log containing any changes to their personal information since the previous year. Logs are made in the following format:
```javascript
//first log
{ name : 'Joe Bloggs',
address : '123 Fake Street',
year : 2007 }

//second log
{ name : 'Joe Doe',
married : true,
year : 2008 }
```
There is no limit on the amount of fields a log can have, nor the field names or values. The only field which is guaranteed to be in each log is the year the log was made, ```year```. If no information changes, a log does not have to be submitted for that year.

Write a function which takes a collection of logs (indeterminate in size, not necessarily in chronological order) and returns a log with the most up to date information for each field. The fields should be in order of their first chronological appearance in a log.

For the example logs above, the expected result would be the following object:
```javascript
{ name: 'Joe Doe',
address: '123 Fake Street',
year: 2008,
married: true }
```
